Definition.WordDefinition: Newcomer \New"com`er\, n. One who has lately come. [1913 Webster]
newcomer n 1: any new participant in some activity [syn: {fledgling}, {fledgeling}, {starter}, {neophyte}, {freshman}, {newbie}, {entrant}] 2: a recent arrival; "he's a newcomer to Boston"
